	<h2 id="compile">Compile your own theme</h2>
	<p>You can use our <a href="https://github.com/space10-community/cf-themes">themes repository</a> to easily create your own theme.</p>
	<p>The steps are as follows:
		<ol>
			<li>Clone the repository.</li>
			<li>Run <pre class="inline">$ npm install</pre> to install dependencies (Conversational Form).</li>
			<li>Add your own theme.scss in /themes (see list of variables <a href="https://github.com/space10-community/conversational-form/blob/master/src/styles/_cf-variables.scss">here</a>.</li>
			<li>Copy space10-theme.html and replace the .css refence to match to name of the theme file you just created.</li>
			<li>Time to start building: <pre class="inline">$ gulp watch</pre>. Output will be in the /build folder.</li>
		</ol>
	<p>

